# Web Crawler Configuration

## Deployment
- Namespace: default
- Service name: web-crawler
- Path prefix: /crawler
- Access points:
  - API: http://home.server:30081/crawler/
  - Swagger UI: http://home.server:30081/crawler/docs
  - ReDoc UI: http://home.server:30081/crawler/redoc

## Configuration
- Memory threshold: 80% (configurable)
- Debug logging: CRAWLER_DEBUG environment variable
- Storage options:
  - Redis for caching
  - PostgreSQL for persistence

## Monitoring
```bash
# Status check
kubectl get pods -n default -l app=web-crawler

# Logs
kubectl logs -n default -l app=web-crawler --tail=100

# Configuration
kubectl get configmap -n default web-crawler-config -o yaml
```

## Best Practices
1. Use deployment script for updates
2. Monitor memory usage through debug logs
3. Configure appropriate cleanup intervals
4. Set proper log levels per environment
5. Monitor storage backend health 